{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/breathlessness/background-information/definition/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"32e9299e-07ae-50a7-a4e2-8e4143b99446","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6b879473-6e2f-43f4-bbf4-9f448ade2e40 --><h2>What is it?</h2><!-- end field 6b879473-6e2f-43f4-bbf4-9f448ade2e40 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 8e7c2aa4-d3fd-4a2c-a8b3-f3dfedde9a03 --><!-- begin field baa921af-d148-411c-9e80-93ce95c9bb13 --><ul><li><strong>Breathlessness</strong>, also known as dyspnoea, is a subjective, usually distressing sensation or awareness of difficulty with breathing.</li><li><strong>Breathlessness can be classified </strong>by its speed of onset as:<ul><li><strong>Acute breathlessness </strong>— when it develops over minutes.</li><li><strong>Subacute breathlessness </strong>— when it develops over hours or days.</li><li><strong>Chronic breathlessness </strong>— when it develops over weeks or months.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/breathlessness/references/\">Hopkin, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/breathlessness/references/\">BMJ, 2015</a>]</p><!-- end field baa921af-d148-411c-9e80-93ce95c9bb13 --><!-- end item 8e7c2aa4-d3fd-4a2c-a8b3-f3dfedde9a03 -->","topic":{"id":"6759b170-256d-53ce-9432-aabc4a6cdad1","topicId":"3816dff2-9844-4422-bc4f-062669a6f4d9","topicName":"Breathlessness","slug":"breathlessness","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2020","chapters":[{"id":"e9c86c03-c78a-5c76-acf7-dc612bf8c6a4","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b4534171-48a6-59f3-90e8-20991ee537b7","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"704593b6-5c14-5a20-96b8-8cab6b955b0f","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","